        "text": "For each supported connected cooling appliance in the applicable product scope, the app shall display the manufacturer-defined appliance type as a human-readable label on the dashboard.",
        "happyFlow": "A user opens the dashboard and each supported connected cooling appliance is shown with the appliance type label provided by the appliance data source.",
        "alternativeFlows": [
          "If multiple supported cooling appliances are present, the app displays the corresponding manufacturer-defined appliance type label for each appliance independently."
        ],
        "exceptionFlows": [
          "If the manufacturer-defined appliance type is not available for an appliance, the app displays a defined fallback label indicating that the appliance type is unavailable, without preventing the dashboard from loading."
        ],
        "acceptanceCriteria": [
          "Given the dashboard contains a supported connected cooling appliance with a manufacturer-defined appliance type, when the dashboard is displayed, then the appliance tile or list entry shows that appliance type as a readable text label.",
          "Given the dashboard contains multiple supported connected cooling appliances with different manufacturer-defined appliance types, when the dashboard is displayed, then each appliance shows its own appliance type label and no label is assigned to the wrong appliance.",
          "Given the manufacturer-defined appliance type for an appliance changes in the appliance data source, when the dashboard data is refreshed, then the dashboard displays the updated appliance type label for that appliance.",
          "Given the manufacturer-defined appliance type is unavailable for an appliance, when the dashboard is displayed, then the appliance remains visible and the type field shows a defined unavailable fallback instead of an empty, misleading, or incorrect type label."
        ],
