        "id": "SR_REQ_1.2.1",
        "text": "For each supported connected cooling appliance in the applicable product scope, the app shall display the appliance's current overall status on the dashboard using the status categories normal operation, unavailable, and requires user attention.",
        "happyFlow": "A user opens the dashboard and each supported connected cooling appliance is shown with its current overall status category.",
        "alternativeFlows": [
          "If the appliance status is normal operation, the dashboard indicates that the appliance is operating normally.",
          "If the appliance status is unavailable, the dashboard indicates that the appliance is unavailable.",
          "If the appliance status requires user attention, the dashboard indicates that user attention is required."
        ],
        "exceptionFlows": [
          "If the current overall status cannot be retrieved, the app displays the appliance status as unavailable or as a defined unknown-status fallback without preventing the dashboard from loading."
        ],
        "acceptanceCriteria": [
          "Given a supported connected cooling appliance has the current overall status normal operation, when the dashboard is displayed, then the appliance entry shows the normal operation status.",
          "Given a supported connected cooling appliance has the current overall status unavailable, when the dashboard is displayed, then the appliance entry shows the unavailable status.",
          "Given a supported connected cooling appliance has the current overall status requires user attention, when the dashboard is displayed, then the appliance entry shows the requires user attention status.",
          "Given multiple supported connected cooling appliances have different current overall statuses, when the dashboard is displayed, then each appliance entry shows the status belonging to that appliance.",
          "Given the current overall status of an appliance changes in the appliance data source, when the dashboard data is refreshed, then the dashboard displays the updated status for that appliance.",
          "Given the current overall status cannot be retrieved for an appliance, when the dashboard is displayed, then the appliance remains visible and the status area shows unavailable or a defined unknown-status fallback instead of a misleading normal operation status."
        ],
