        "id": "SR_REQ_2.8.2",
        "text": "For applicable connected appliances that include a controllable refrigeration zone, the appliance detail page shall allow an authorized user to apply a selected refrigeration-zone target temperature value from 2 °C through 9 °C in 1 °C increments.",
        "happyFlow": "An authorized user selects a permitted refrigeration-zone target temperature and applies it; the system submits the target-temperature change for the refrigeration zone and reflects the confirmed result when reported by the appliance.",
        "alternativeFlows": [
          "If the selected value is the same as the current confirmed target temperature, the system may either prevent a redundant apply action or process it without changing the confirmed target temperature."
        ],
        "exceptionFlows": [
          "If a submitted value is outside 2 °C through 9 °C or is not a 1 °C increment, the system rejects the value and does not send it as an appliance control command.",
          "If the target-temperature change fails, is rejected, or times out, the system informs the user that the change was not confirmed and preserves or reloads the last confirmed refrigeration-zone target temperature.",
          "If the user is not authorized to control the appliance, the system rejects the apply action and does not send an appliance control command."
        ],
        "acceptanceCriteria": [
          "Given an authorized user selects any permitted value V from 2 °C through 9 °C in 1 °C increments and activates apply, then the system submits a refrigeration-zone target-temperature change request with value V in degrees Celsius for the selected appliance.",
          "Given the appliance confirms the target-temperature change to V, when the appliance detail page data is refreshed or updated from confirmed appliance state, then the displayed refrigeration-zone target temperature is V °C.",
          "Given the target-temperature change request is accepted for processing but not yet confirmed by the appliance, then the page shall not present the new value as confirmed until confirmation is received.",
          "Given a value below 2 °C, above 9 °C, or with a fractional increment is submitted through the UI or API, then the system rejects the request and does not dispatch a refrigeration-zone target-temperature command to the appliance.",
          "Given the appliance or backend rejects the command, the command fails, or confirmation times out, then the page informs the user that the change was not confirmed and the confirmed refrigeration-zone target temperature remains the last confirmed value.",
          "Given a user without control authorization attempts to apply a refrigeration-zone target temperature, then the system rejects the action and no appliance control command is sent."
        ],
